x4freetext: THE 2H(3HE,GAMMA)5LI CROSS SECTION HAS BEEN MEASURED AT
TO EXCITATION ENERGIES IN 5LI OF 17-26 MEV.
GAMMA-RAY ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS WERE MEASURED AT
SEVERAL ENERGIES IN THIS RANGE. TRANSITION INTENSITIES
TO THE GROUND STATE (G0) AND FIRST EXCITED STATE (G1)
OF LI-5 WERE EXTRACTED,AND THE RESULTS WERE COMPARED
TO THEORETICAL PREDICTIONS. THE G0 AND G1 RESULTS WERE
FOUND TO BE CONSISTENT WITH A 1/2+ STATE NEAR 18 MEV
AND A 5/2+ STATE NEAR 21 MEV IN LI-5.
EVIDENCE WAS ALSO FOUND FOR HIGHER-LYING STATES, SOME
OF WHICH MIGHT HAVE NEGATIVE PARITY.
